## (individual) Future for advanced use of OpenBIM

### HUGO

#### Are you likely to use OpenBIM tools in your thesis?

I am not likely to use the tools themselves directly in my thesis, as my study track in Belgium is less focused on BIM and coding, and more oriented towards architectural and urban context. However, I will take many lessons from this course into my thesis work. The assignments taught me to approach problems in a different, more structured way, and I now clearly see the value of BIM and the relationship between code and model. Even if I do not use the tools explicitly, the mindset and analytical methods will definitely influence my thesis.

#### Are you likely to use OpenBIM tools in your professional life in the next 10 years?

If I work in the field of architecture, it is very likely that I will encounter OpenBIM tools, as the industry is becoming increasingly digital. More and more aspects of the design and construction process are described through algorithms, data, and models. Because of this ongoing evolution, there is a strong possibility that I will use OpenBIM tools in my professional practice.

#### Wrap up

At the start of the course, I felt quite overwhelmed by the concept of BIM. I wasn’t entirely sure what the purpose of the course was or what we were ultimately working towards. However, as my focus area was architecture, I gradually became more familiar with the material and started to get a better grasp of the overall direction. I began to understand how a piece of developed code could be applied to a spatial model and how the two related.

Assignment A3, however, was more challenging. I ran into many coding issues, as well as imperfections in the IFC model. These obstacles made progress difficult. Eventually, I regained clarity by returning to what I am most familiar with: the architectural perspective. By fully analysing the IFC model its, I developed a much better understanding of what was happening in the code and why certain things had not worked initially.

This approach also helps me understand the feedback we received on our tutorial—that our tool was at times too specific. That specificity largely came from the fact that we solved problems based on one particular model and then incorporated those solutions directly into the code.

Looking back, I’m glad that this course helped me see the value of BIM. I will definitely take this way of thinking with me in the future.

### LISANNE

#### Are you likely to use OpenBIM tools in your thesis?

If possible, I would like to use OpenBIM tools in my thesis, as they are highly relevant to my studies in Belgium. By integrating these tools, I could analyze the technical aspects of certain buildings and perform faster, additional checks using digital models. I find this particularly interesting, and I believe that OpenBIM will become increasingly important in the architecture sector. Therefore, exploring these tools in more depth would be a valuable addition to my research.

#### Are you likely to use OpenBIM tools in your professional life in the next 10 years?

Because I aim to work as an architectural engineer and would like to perform structural calculations in my future career, I believe that OpenBIM tools can be highly useful. These tools can help accelerate progress in the construction industry and enable us to design and build in a much more optimized way.

#### Wrap up

Because this was my first real introduction to the concept of BIM, I initially felt quite overwhelmed and didn’t really know what to expect. The course content seemed a bit vague at first, and it felt as though I was missing some background information. However, after going through the course website, I began to understand the purpose of the course much better. Being part of the architecture focus group also made me feel more at ease, since I already had a lot of background knowledge in that area. Writing the first code in Assignment 1 helped me grasp the idea of coding linked to model checking.

Assignment 2 also went very smoothly: creating the flowchart was much easier thanks to the background knowledge I had gained in previous years. Assignment 3, on the other hand, was more challenging. Writing the longer piece of code was far less straightforward, partly because I haven’t had much exposure to programming in recent years, and partly because the model contained some complexities that made certain checks more difficult. In the end, these challenges led me to gain even more insights into IFC models and how they should ideally be structured. Through this assignment, I improved both my coding skills and my understanding of BIM models.

The feedback we received after the tutorial provided additional insights, both regarding the code and the way it was presented. I learned that such a tool would be even more effective if it could operate on a much larger scale, linked to more functionalities and capable of analyzing many different models. This would allow us to check buildings much more efficiently.

Reflecting on this course has made me realize how much I have learned and how valuable these skills will be in the future. It has also motivated me to explore this field further, as I believe it will continue to grow and become an increasingly important part of the construction industry.

